00:26:36,313 --> 00:26:41,078
but new things can sprout from that soil or, you know, emerge like a zombie, whatever.

434
00:26:41,939 --> 00:26:47,184
These two models are in no way the only options for romantic and erotic narrative design,

435
00:26:47,724 --> 00:26:52,109
and there you can probably point out to games that are already using them at least to some degree.

436
00:26:52,559 --> 00:26:54,960
But I hope they'll still be useful frameworks for you all.

437
00:26:56,120 --> 00:26:58,901
I feel like they're great ways to take this tarnished kindness

438
00:26:58,941 --> 00:27:02,182
coin dynamic and reforge it with writing and narrative design

439
00:27:02,322 --> 00:27:03,183
into something better.

440
00:27:03,203 --> 00:27:05,744
And I also feel like they're great ways

441
00:27:05,844 --> 00:27:08,464
to tell different stories about love and desire,

442
00:27:08,645 --> 00:27:11,165
whether it's those forces as unstoppable

443
00:27:11,626 --> 00:27:14,346
or whether it's just little impossible daily miracles.

444
00:27:14,847 --> 00:27:16,887
Both visions can be beautiful and compelling.

445
00:27:17,348 --> 00:27:18,568
It just falls on you and your team

446
00:27:18,608 --> 00:27:20,248
to decide which works best for your game.

447
00:27:21,049 --> 00:27:21,889
So to sum up.

448
00:27:22,563 --> 00:27:24,383
Go for chemistry, not bland niceness.

449
00:27:24,963 --> 00:27:26,424
Give your NPCs agency.

450
00:27:27,164 --> 00:27:29,825
Use every game system to tell love and sex stories.

